title: MI Fatbike State Championship p/b Rocky Mountain Bikes
Ann Arbor Spring Training Series
description: For 2017, the Ann Arbor Spring Training Series is a part of the USA Cycling BEGINNING RACER PROGRAM (BRP). This five-week series of clinics and practice races is designed to provide new racers with a fun and structured introduction to bike racing so they can learn and practice the core skills and information for safer and better racing. New riders will learn from licensed coaches and experienced racers, and they will earn upgrade 2 points per week for participating in the clinic and race. Cat. 4 women are welcome to participate! More details are at www.SpringTrainingSeries.com.
course: Course is 1-km loop along Varsity Dr. (south off Ellsworth Rd., Ann Arbor, MI) and Highland Dr. Two 90- degree corners, two sweeping curves.
registration: Pre-register online: There are no online processing fees and it makes check-in and results easier for everyone! The pre-registration link is open until 8:00 PM ET the evening before each race. Day-of-race: Add $5; open until 15 min. before start.
directions: Parking/registration at 1180 E Ellsworth Rd, Ann Arbor, MI 48108.

Sean Stanton Memorial Community Slow Roll
description: The Second Annual Sean Stanton Memorial Community Slow Roll will be held  Friday, July 14th at City Hall in Mt. Pleasant, Michigan 48858 starting at 6:30 PM.
course: The course will wind its way from city hall, head to CMU campus, wind its way through campus and return to city hall parking lot. The course will be approximately 3 miles long.
registration: Registration will be handled on site in the area next to the parking lot by Mt. Pleasant City Hall.  Registration opens at 5:30 PM until 6:30 PM when the Slow Roll starts.
notes: All slow roll participants should arrive at 5:30 and all must wear helmets. Children under 9 years of age must be accompanied by an adult. The Slow Roll will start at the Mt. Pleasant, City Hall parking lot at 6:30.  participants will be organized and lined up.   Police escort will be provided during the slow roll to assure rider safety.
directions: Mt. Pleasant City Hall is located in downtown Mt. Pleasant, MI at 320 Broadway Street between Main Street and Pine Street.  City Hall is one mile north from the Central Michigan University campus.

title: Cherry Roubaix
description: 2017 Cherry Roubaix Gran Fondo.  It's a tour!  It's a race.  It's a celebration of bikes spanning Grand Traverse and Leelanau County's over some of the most scenic and challenging topography in the Midwest.
course: Three courses to choose from: 1) a twenty mile rid along the traffic free route then the last 5 along quiet, scenic country roads.  2) a 55 mile route with stunning views of Grand Traverse Bay, Lake Michigan, Manitou Island and over 3,000 feet of climbing.  3) and 86 mile route including the 55 but adding the top of Leelanau Peninsula including Northport and about 5,000 feet of ascent.  All routes can be toured or raced and are well marked with lead and follow cars, and food and beverage stops.  All events end on the same finish line on top of Herman Hill.
registration: Go to www.cherry-roubaix.com for a link to registration and other information about the 10th annual Cherry Roubaix.
directions: The Cherry Roubaix Gran Fondo starts on Front Street in front of the historic State Theatre in Traverse City and has a police escort along Grand Traverse Bay to M-22 and out into Leelanau County.  All routes end in Sutton's Bay with a party at Hop Lot.
